        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> @tarruda If making it synchronous from the user point of view is required it is enough to just disable <C-\\><C-n> as it is the only way to exit terminal mode.\n\nNo, see [the implementation](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/ex_docmd.c#L9420-L9423). It uses `termopen()` and `:startinsert` which means nvim will first finish processing all commands and only when it restarts the normal mode command loop it will enter terminal mode.\n\nBy synchronous I meant a version of `:shell` that only returns when the program exits(Unless `:shell` is already asynchronous, if so then nevermind)\n",
